{"body": "Following comments by @jweslley and @pwightman I have added inequalities to WhereChain in this pull request: https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8453\r\n\r\nRegarding this commit, I have a couple of questions for @rafaelfranca and @carlosantoniodasilva : \r\n\r\n* are you okay with aliasing each method to exist both in the short and long form, e.g.: `greater_than` and `gt`? I feel that users will expect both formats\r\n\r\n* most of the methods inside `WhereChain` look similar: do you like them as they are (separate method that repeat some code), or would your rather have them refactored with some metaprogramming?", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/11138557", "created_at": "2012-12-07T17:28:32Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8332#issuecomment-11138557", "updated_at": "2012-12-07T17:28:32Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 8332, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/claudiob/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/claudiob/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/claudiob/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/claudiob", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/claudiob/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/claudiob", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/claudiob/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/4dea5cf83d2d6c1228750b76e579b38d?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F11ed516444b2593eaba7f2c2bb63483e.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/claudiob/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/claudiob/received_events", "gravatar_id": "4dea5cf83d2d6c1228750b76e579b38d", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/claudiob/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "claudiob", "type": "User", "id": 10076, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/claudiob/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "523d97adbd354364b900830d"}, "id": 11138557, "issue_url